  Not compatible (inbound):
    Proprietary licenses that restrict redistribution
    Licenses that prohibit commercial use
    Licenses with field-of-use restrictions
    Business Source License (BSL/BUSL) variants

When this license conflicts with an inbound license, the inbound license
governs its own component and this license governs the remainder.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OUTBOUND COMPATIBILITY
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Works incorporating components under this license may be distributed as a
whole under GPL v3.0 or AGPL v3.0, provided the conditions of this license
are preserved for the OCPL-licensed portions. The constitutional invariants
(Condition 5) and protocol openness requirements (Condition 1) must be
preserved in any such distribution; they may not be overridden by the terms
of the incorporating license.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EXTENSIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Domain-specific extensions to this license may be adopted alongside the core
conditions. Extensions add conditions; they may not remove or weaken any core
condition. Recognized extensions:

  OCPL-Format  — additional conditions for format/protocol specification
                 projects (open format guarantee, format portability)
  OCPL-Model   — additional conditions for AI model projects (model weights
                 availability, training data lineage, inference access)
  OCPL-Tool    — additional conditions for developer tooling (free tier
                 requirement, CLI/local-mode must remain free)

Extension texts are published at: https://openko.network/ocpl/extensions/

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
COMPLIANCE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you cannot comply with these conditions, you may not distribute or operate
this software. The conditions exist to protect the protocol's openness, users'
sovereignty, and the network's integrity — not to restrict legitimate
commercial activity built on an open foundation.

Non-compliant forks that remove these conditions are not covered works under
this license and are not authorized to use the protocol specifications,
trademarks, or Foundry registry of the originating project.

